The easiest part in Section 1 was learning how to use print() and variables because they were simple and clear to understand. I also enjoyed creating small programs using input() because it made the programs interactive. The hardest part was understanding different data types and when to use each one correctly. During debugging, I once got a SyntaxError because I forgot to close a quotation mark in a string. I fixed it by checking the error line carefully and adding the missing quotation mark. I also learned that the order of lines is important because Python runs code from top to bottom. Before starting Section 2, I will review variables, input/output, data types, and debugging basics to strengthen my foundation.